Morro dos Seis Lagos (Hill of the Six Lakes). Iron canga substrate enriched in niobium and radioactive. No mineral soil; very well drained. Low forest with thin stems resembles caatinga or bana, has strong springy root mat over loose boulders, with thin litter accumulation. Vouchers from forest inventory (1/10 ha. 500 m x 2 m min DBH = 2 cm).
